<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Inference on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/inference/</link><description>Recent content in Inference on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/inference/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Rust Mismatched Types — Type Mismatch Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/type-mismatch-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/type-mismatch-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="mismatched-types--type-mismatch-error"&gt;Mismatched Types — Type Mismatch Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A compiler error with the message &amp;ldquo;mismatched types&amp;rdquo; occurs when you use a value of one type where a different type is expected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust is statically typed — every expression has a known type at compile time. The compiler rejects code where the actual type doesn&amp;rsquo;t match the expected type. Unlike dynamic languages, Rust won&amp;rsquo;t silently convert between most types.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;String vs &amp;amp;str&lt;/strong&gt; — passing &lt;code&gt;String&lt;/code&gt; where &lt;code&gt;&amp;amp;str&lt;/code&gt; is expected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Numeric mixing&lt;/strong&gt; — adding &lt;code&gt;i32&lt;/code&gt; + &lt;code&gt;f64&lt;/code&gt; without casting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wrong return type&lt;/strong&gt; — function returns wrong type.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option vs value&lt;/strong&gt; — passing &lt;code&gt;Option&amp;lt;i32&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; where &lt;code&gt;i32&lt;/code&gt; is expected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Result not unwrapped&lt;/strong&gt; — passing &lt;code&gt;Result&amp;lt;T, E&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; where &lt;code&gt;T&lt;/code&gt; is expected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: String vs &amp;amp;str
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;greet&lt;/span&gt;(name: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;str&lt;/span&gt;) { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hi &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, name); }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; String::from(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;greet(name); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Error: expected &amp;amp;str, found String
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Numeric type mismatch
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; x: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;i32&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; y: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;f64&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3.14&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; sum &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; y; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Error: cannot add f64 to i32
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Wrong return type
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;get_number&lt;/span&gt;() -&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;i32&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;42&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Error: expected i32, found &amp;amp;str
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 4: Bool where int expected
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; flag &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; count: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;i32&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; flag; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Error: expected i32, found bool
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="solutions"&gt;Solutions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-borrow-or-convert-types"&gt;Fix 1: Borrow or convert types&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;greet&lt;/span&gt;(name: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;str&lt;/span&gt;) { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hi &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, name); }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; String::from(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Option A: borrow
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;greet(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;name);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Option B: convert
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;greet(name.as_str());
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-explicit-numeric-casting"&gt;Fix 2: Explicit numeric casting&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; x: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;i32&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; y: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;f64&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3.14&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; sum &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;f64&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; y;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, sum); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// 8.14
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-return-the-correct-type"&gt;Fix 3: Return the correct type&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;get_number&lt;/span&gt;() -&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;i32&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Return a number, not a string
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-into-for-compatible-types"&gt;Fix 4: Use .into() for compatible types&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;greet&lt;/span&gt;(name: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;str&lt;/span&gt;) { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hi &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, name); }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; String::from(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// String implements Into&amp;lt;&amp;amp;str&amp;gt; via deref
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;greet(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;name);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; x: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;i32&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; y: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;bool&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; y;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, result);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Output:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Mismatched Types / Expected X Found Y — Compiler Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/type-error8/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/type-error8/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="mismatched-types--expected-x-found-y"&gt;Mismatched Types / Expected X Found Y&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The error &lt;code&gt;mismatched types: expected X, found Y&lt;/code&gt; occurs when you provide a value of one type where the compiler expects a different type. Rust is statically typed and does not perform implicit type conversions (except for a few safe coercions).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust&amp;rsquo;s strong type system requires explicit type compatibility. The compiler infers types from context, but when two incompatible types are used in the same position, it produces a clear error message showing what was expected and what was found.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Type Mismatch — Mismatched Types Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/type-mismatch/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/type-mismatch/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="type-mismatch--mismatched-types-error"&gt;Type Mismatch — Mismatched Types Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A compiler error with the message &amp;ldquo;mismatched types&amp;rdquo; occurs when you try to use a value of one type where a different type is expected. Rust&amp;rsquo;s strong, static type system prevents this at compile time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust is strongly typed and performs type checking at compile time. The &amp;ldquo;mismatched types&amp;rdquo; error appears when:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A function receives the wrong argument type.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A variable is assigned a value of the wrong type.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A return value doesn&amp;rsquo;t match the declared return type.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pattern matching arms return different types.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Numeric types are mixed without explicit conversion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unlike dynamically typed languages, Rust won&amp;rsquo;t implicitly convert between most types. You must be explicit about type conversions.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>